Objective and High-level Overview

The central government of UAE has issued a circular that all licence Financial Institutions must launch the Jaywan cobage cards.

Banks issuing MasterCard or Visa card must in future issue a co-badged card with either MasterCard of visa and this is with respect to the centre Bank mandate reference number 5480 2024 according to which cards must support with both domestic as well as International transactions.

The card routing must be accordingly configured.

These cards will be configured with 8 digit Bank identification numbers. Hence all the bank's systems will need to ensure that these BINs are configured, identified, accepted, processed.

Jaywan cobadged cards with international card schemes will meet market meets and aspirations with comparative value added services and at a reduce cost.
